      "raw_text": "of early placer diggings which were\nvery rich,\n\n\nOther men are already coming in\nwith gold and others are rushing to\nthe scene.\n\n\nThree men in one day pounded out\n$500. This wonderful record is be-\nlieved not to have been exceeded even\nin the palmy days of California and\nthere certainly never has been any\nthink like it in Oregon.\n\n\nSeveral other men have arrived from\nGreyback mountain with large guam\ntitles of gold. which they have pound\ned out and washed out of the quartz,\nand it is said the country is being stalk\ned in every direction."
